-- Leoni Raises Company's 2010 Forecasts as Automotive Sector Orders Increase
-- Mike Gavin
-- 2010-07-23T06:09:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-23/leoni-raises-company-s-2010-forecasts-as-automotive-sector-orders-increase.html

          
          
             Leoni AG , the German maker of 
automotive electrical cables, raised its 2010 sales and earnings 
forecast, with the projected earnings before interest and taxes 
doubled to 100 million euros ($129 million), the company said.   
 It now expects to generate sales of 2.6 billion euros 
to 2.7 billion euros, Leoni said.  
          
          


  


        